Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.12,0:02:32.15,Spica - Title,,0,0,90,,Memory of a Distant Day
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.11,0:24:36.14,Spica - Title,,0,0,90,,Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.18,0:24:59.93,Spica - Title,,0,0,0,,My Mother's Face
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.23,0:01:54.07,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,My dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.07,0:01:56.86,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Year 1, Class 1, Kamogawa Asumi
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.65,0:02:01.87,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,My dream is to become a rocket driver!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.20,0:02:06.87,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,That's because I've heard that the Earth is very\Npretty when you look at it from space.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.87,0:02:11.38,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,So I want to become a rocket driver and go into space!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.00,0:02:15.38,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I want to take people to all sorts of different planets!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.46,0:02:19.38,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,And when they're on my rocket...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.38,0:02:23.89,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,...my dad and Lion-san will get special free rides!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.60,0:02:25.68,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,The end!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.62,0:02:46.04,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,W-Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.04,0:02:47.41,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Why dominoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.41,0:02:50.33,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,These have nothing to do with being an astronaut!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.62,0:02:53.25,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Ah, it's no good. This is complete nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.63,0:02:55.88,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,What's in this box?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.59,0:03:02.72,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I should've known...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.76,0:03:07.01,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Use all of the dominoes in the boxes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.02,0:03:10.14,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,...to make a domino line ready to be toppled\Nwithin the seven days allotted.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.48,0:03:12.69,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,What? With all of these!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.27,0:03:15.07,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,You've got to be kidding me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.07,0:03:17.94,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,What are they trying to make us do with this exam?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.53,0:03:20.28,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,They want to make us line up dominoes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.61,0:03:22.91,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.49,0:03:25.37,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.99,0:03:27.79,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,So that's what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.62,0:03:33.33,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Asumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.46,0:03:38.92,Spica - Italic,,0,0,90,,Lion-san told me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.59,0:03:46.93,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,The most important qualities for an astronaut to have...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.31,0:03:50.93,Spica - Italic,,0,0,90,,They must be trying to test those here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.56,0:03:58.65,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Hey now, Asumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.65,0:04:01.49,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Don't tell me this thing has gotten to you already?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.49,0:04:03.11,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,That's not it, Kei-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.11,0:04:05.28,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,It just got a little fun for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.74,0:04:07.87,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,What? Fun!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.49,0:04:10.37,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Yes. Very!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.91,0:04:15.04,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Asumi, you really are a strange one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.04,0:04:16.13,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.42,0:04:19.38,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,No there's no need to apologize, it's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.63,0:04:24.38,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,You think this is going to be fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.23,0:04:38.19,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.24,0:04:43.24,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,What? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.24,0:04:45.07,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Is this some sort of emergency?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.49,0:04:49.91,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,It's probably just time for lights out, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.91,0:04:53.50,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,What? If that's all, they should say\Nso before turning out the lights!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.67,0:04:58.44,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Now then... Asumi, where do you wanna sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.44,0:05:01.05,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I'm fine with whatever is left after you two choose.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.84,0:05:04.67,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Well then, sorry, but could you let me take the bottom bunk?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.34,0:05:08.26,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I'm really bad about sleeping in high places.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.39,0:05:11.51,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Ah, which one do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.44,0:05:23.53,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Really, she could at least answer us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.70,0:05:29.41,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I dunno how to put it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.95,0:05:33.49,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,...but these beds are so compressed that\Nit's almost hard to breathe in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.87,0:05:35.00,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.00,0:05:38.42,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Hey, you know, we still haven't heard her name.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.42,0:05:39.50,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,That girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.38,0:05:41.04,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.54,0:05:43.46,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,It would be hard to ask now...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.76,0:05:45.01,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Should we just give her a nickname?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.01,0:05:46.76,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Think about it, Asumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.76,0:05:51.22,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Well... her hairpin is cute, so how about Pinko-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.68,0:05:54.39,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Pinko!? That's a little...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.39,0:05:56.14,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Isn't there anything else we could use?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.69,0:05:59.06,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Ukita Marika.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.86,0:06:02.19,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I won't say it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.23,0:06:06.78,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Right. Then, how should we address you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.36,0:06:11.16,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Whatever. You can use my family name.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.41,0:06:14.41,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Kamogawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.00,0:06:19.87,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,What did you mean when you said that there\Nwas no way that you would be wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.50,0:06:22.21,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Ah, what do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.92,0:06:24.38,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,The room number.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.80,0:06:27.88,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,There's no way I could be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.34,0:06:31.89,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,At that time, you didn't hesitate at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.89,0:06:33.93,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Ah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.93,0:06:39.81,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,You know, all of the numbers written\Non the rooms are distances to stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.86,0:06:45.40,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,This room is the distance to my favorite star...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.48,0:06:51.36,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,The distance to Spica, which Lion-san told me long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.28,0:06:53.78,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,350 light years.{Wikipedia says it's 260 ± 20 ly actually}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.79,0:06:58.04,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,Ah, I found Spica!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.37,0:07:00.71,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,Wow. Very well done, little one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.58,0:07:04.84,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,It's out there, 350 light years away!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.92,0:07:10.55,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,That's right. Shining so beautifully that\Nit was also known as the "pearl star."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.55,0:07:14.01,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,It's the alpha star in the constellation Virgo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.01,0:07:16.81,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,But there's a secret behind that star.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.81,0:07:17.81,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,Secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.60,0:07:22.19,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,Actually, Spica isn't just one star...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.19,0:07:24.06,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,...it's something called a binary star.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.06,0:07:25.31,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,Binary star?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.32,0:07:27.90,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,Yes, a binary star.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.90,0:07:33.53,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,Two stars rotate around, chasing\Neach other at incredible speeds...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.53,0:07:38.62,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,...so if you look at it from as far away\Nas Earth, they look like one big star.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.37,0:07:45.17,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,Anyhow, their rotation speed is so high that\Nthe stars aren't perfectly circular...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.17,0:07:47.13,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,...but actually oval-shaped instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.21,0:07:53.97,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,The twin Spicas support each other\Nto give birth to that radiance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.30,0:07:59.64,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,They'll continue on and on like\Nthat until one of them disappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.31,0:08:05.94,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,What's wrong, little one?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.94,0:08:08.57,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,Was that explanation too difficult for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.73,0:08:12.03,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,Lion-san, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.03,0:08:15.11,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,You aren't going to disappear and go off anywhere, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.12,0:08:17.45,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,We'll always, always be together, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.41,0:08:22.58,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,Yeah. I won't be going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.04,0:08:25.96,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,As long as there are stars up there, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.30,0:08:35.18,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,It's like I'm a princess!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.52,0:08:42.68,Spica - Flashback,,0,0,90,,Asumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.68,0:08:44.98,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Asumi! Asumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.69,0:08:49.69,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Asumi! Come on, Asumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.40,0:08:55.20,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,It's morning, Asumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.41,0:09:00.37,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Good morning, Lion-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.16,0:09:02.45,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Lion?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.45,0:09:04.87,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,What are you sleep-talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.04,0:09:07.96,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Come on, stand up! Let's go wash your face!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.96,0:09:10.09,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,I can walk by myself, Kei-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.09,0:09:12.71,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Just come with me. One, two! One, two!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.92,0:09:16.88,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Good morning, Ukita-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.31,0:09:21.22,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Good morning
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.81,0:09:27.85,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,She really does rub me the wrong way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.73,0:09:33.48,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I'm sure she's just shy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.49,0:09:37.95,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Huh? She's just a contrary neat-freak!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.95,0:09:41.70,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Ukita-san just kind of reminds me of someone I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.70,0:09:42.45,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.37,0:09:45.79,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,A friend I used to play with...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.79,0:09:46.87,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Just the atmosphere about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.62,0:09:49.38,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Kasane-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.09,0:09:53.46,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,I couldn't understand how she felt...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.46,0:09:55.84,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,...and I ended up hurting her very badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.39,0:10:04.26,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,But I think I could understand her a little bit better now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.27,0:10:07.27,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Not with words, but with feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.85,0:10:12.73,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Also, it may just be coincidence that we\Nended up together, but since we're here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.73,0:10:14.90,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I'd rather be friends with everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.90,0:10:16.69,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Kei-san, and Ukita-san both.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.33,0:10:25.41,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Well then, let's get breakfast out of the\Nway and get started on those dominoes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.41,0:10:26.29,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.91,0:10:28.96,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Or so I said...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.42,0:10:32.50,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,But looking at how many there are,\NI can't help but feel a little depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.50,0:10:34.80,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Where's the paper that had the\Nproject procedures written on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.05,0:10:37.01,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Ah, I have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.92,0:10:40.30,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Use all of the dominoes in the boxes...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.30,0:10:42.43,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,...to make a domino line ready to be\Ntoppled within the seven days allotted.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.43,0:10:44.60,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,You are free to line them up however you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.60,0:10:48.43,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,However, there should be one line\Nconnecting the start and finish points.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.06,0:10:51.60,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Hm, within seven days, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.60,0:10:53.27,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Is there something wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.98,0:10:57.74,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I wonder what we're supposed to do if we finish before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.61,0:11:01.57,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,They wouldn't give us a project that we would finish too early!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.57,0:11:03.20,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,That's true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.20,0:11:05.70,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Hold on, there might be something written in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.33,0:11:09.75,Spica - Italic,,0,0,90,,It's certainly true that seven days is\Na long time for something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.42,0:11:14.63,Spica - Italic,,0,0,90,,So that means that there must be something\Nthat won't let us finish in seven days?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.47,0:11:23.09,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Ít doesn't look like there is anything else written about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.09,0:11:25.30,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Well, I guess we should just give it a shot, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.39,0:11:31.06,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Also, it looks like we can manually\Npush that box into the wall there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.78,0:11:44.57,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,How many times does that make, Kamogawa-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.03,0:11:46.49,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.49,0:11:48.49,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,You don't have to worry about it, Asumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.50,0:11:51.58,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,It was because we thought that might happen that we're lining them up separately.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.96,0:11:53.12,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.12,0:11:57.46,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,When we're making them into one long line later, we'll have to be more careful though.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.09,0:12:02.42,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,But really, I wish they had at least\Ngiven us some stoppers too. Really...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.24,0:12:27.03,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,With this much done, it's looking more like we might get that break that you were talking about, Asumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.03,0:12:29.24,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,This isn't as big of a deal as I thought it would be.
Comment: 0,0:12:44.15,0:12:54.21,Spica - Main,,0,0,0,,Eyecatch
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.02,0:12:58.19,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Ah, this is so irritating!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.19,0:13:04.74,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Why do we have to tediously line up dominoes,\Nclosed up in a room with just us three guys!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.16,0:13:08.16,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I didn't come here to do these tedious little projects!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.16,0:13:10.16,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I came here to do something bigger!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.70,0:13:13.27,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Really, you've been really obnoxious lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.27,0:13:15.41,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Get working on this some more, you moron.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.83,0:13:17.83,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Who's a moron, you little...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.83,0:13:20.29,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,You with the monk haircut over there, moron.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.71,0:13:22.71,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,What'd you say, you little...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.72,0:13:28.72,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Do you understand what will happen if you get me mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.18,0:13:33.72,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I can have you all drop out alongside me with a push of this button, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.69,0:13:37.60,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Wh-What is it, Suzuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.81,0:13:40.52,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Just try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.52,0:13:42.32,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I won't have any mercy beating the crap out of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.61,0:13:44.53,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,It was just a joke, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.28,0:13:46.82,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Don't get all scary like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.25,0:13:56.04,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,You shouldn't get so serious about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.54,0:14:02.67,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Hey, Suzuki, why did you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.67,0:14:04.88,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,You can call me Shuu, Fuchuuya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.67,0:14:09.13,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Suzuki, why did you want to get into this school?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.22,0:14:13.66,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I told you to call me Shuu...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.66,0:14:14.97,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Don't stop working, moron.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.60,0:14:18.56,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Well, everyone wants to go into space, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.02,0:14:21.81,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,"Right?" Who are we talking about, here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.69,0:14:26.49,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Oh? Then why did you want to come here, Fuchuuya-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.70,0:14:30.41,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I don't want to tell someone like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.53,0:14:32.37,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Ah, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.24,0:14:36.00,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Could it be a little seagull that's the surprising reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.00,0:14:36.83,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.83,0:14:39.00,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Oh, It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.63,0:14:43.79,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,For me, it would have to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.80,0:14:48.01,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,The photo that Armstrong took of the first moon landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.59,0:14:52.43,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I got the feeling that I was on the moon myself from it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.43,0:14:55.39,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,...and I was pretty moved by it, even as a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.02,0:14:59.39,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Buzz Aldrin, standing at the edge of a small crater...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.94,0:15:02.27,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Humanity's first step...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.77,0:15:05.32,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,The pale blue Earth floating above the horizon...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.61,0:15:09.82,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,With my personality, looking at it like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.82,0:15:12.28,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,I couldn't just leave it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.87,0:15:18.29,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I thought that I'd love to take my own picture\Nof the Earth just floating up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.75,0:15:20.04,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.04,0:15:22.37,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Well, that's my motive, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.38,0:15:23.79,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,How about you, Asumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.92,0:15:29.01,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Ah... Going to space has been a dream\Nof mine ever since I was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.01,0:15:32.01,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I wanted to become a rocket driver!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.01,0:15:33.93,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,A rocket driver?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.35,0:15:36.56,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Call it a pilot, at least!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.52,0:15:40.02,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Someone else told me the same thing once!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.02,0:15:41.60,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Most people would say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.44,0:15:45.61,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Um, how about you, Ukita-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.02,0:15:48.86,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Why did you want to get into this school?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.86,0:15:50.19,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,It has nothing to do with you, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.20,0:15:52.40,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Could you please be quiet now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.41,0:15:55.62,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,You happen to talk a lot in your sleep, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.37,0:15:59.66,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,You don't have to worry about that, Asumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.66,0:16:03.04,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I'm not bothered by a little talking in your sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.04,0:16:05.42,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I guess I really do talk a lot in my sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.42,0:16:06.79,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Just a little...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.80,0:16:09.25,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Really, it's nothing to worry about, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.26,0:16:13.76,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,That's right. Compared to your nocturnal\Ntooth grinding, it's pretty cute at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.43,0:16:17.89,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Asumi, do I grind my teeth at night!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.35,0:16:19.39,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Ah, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.14,0:16:22.31,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,You do it a little bit, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.31,0:16:23.85,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,That's "a little bit"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.90,0:16:27.11,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,That's the first time anyone's told me that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.11,0:16:30.19,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,What a shock! I can never get married now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.15,0:16:32.90,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I told you to be quiet already.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.78,0:16:36.03,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Ah, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.83,0:16:38.03,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.74,0:18:04.66,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Finally halfway done, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.66,0:18:05.45,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.04,0:18:08.62,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I'm really sorry, that was all my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.63,0:18:10.33,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,No, there's no helping it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.34,0:18:14.59,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Also, I think that they gave us seven days because\Nthey figured that things like this would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.59,0:18:15.96,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Right. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.80,0:18:20.89,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,But now that four days have passed,\Nthis really has gotten annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.89,0:18:23.18,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,We don't know what the weather is like outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.18,0:18:26.31,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,...and I feel like the pilot who asked them to put a window in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.35,0:18:30.23,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Just what meaning is there to doing this, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.23,0:18:33.19,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,It's useless to think there's any kind of meaning to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.19,0:18:38.24,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,This is just an overly difficult project that they're using to weed people out since there were so many applicants.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.82,0:18:42.07,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,You really are a dry woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.08,0:18:44.16,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,As parched as the Gobi Desert, you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.95,0:18:46.95,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I thought I should say something earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.96,0:18:49.16,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,...but would you start addressing me by name?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.50,0:18:53.21,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Huh? Then what do you want me to call you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.21,0:18:56.80,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Shall I call you Lady Marika or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.80,0:18:58.13,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,You neat-freak.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.80,0:19:01.84,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Kei-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.98,0:19:17.53,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,What are you doing!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.53,0:19:19.65,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Why don't you cool your head off a little?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.65,0:19:20.82,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,You little...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.82,0:19:22.20,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,How dare you do that to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.20,0:19:23.70,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I only called you a neat-freak.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.87,0:19:25.62,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Stop it, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.91,0:19:29.00,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Say that once more, why don't you?\NI won't let you off easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.00,0:19:32.42,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I'll say it as many times as I want, you neat-freak neat-freak neat-freak!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.00,0:19:34.21,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,You've done it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.34,0:19:35.67,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Please, stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.67,0:19:39.67,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,First off, whose fault do you think it was\Nthat we had to do that all over?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.38,0:19:39.67,Spica - Italic,,0,0,90,,Why? We should all be after the same dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.67,0:19:41.43,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I wasn't the only one to do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.59,0:19:43.59,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Don't group us together!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.01,0:19:43.59,Spica - Italic,,0,0,90,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.77,0:19:52.60,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.57,0:19:56.48,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,The dominoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.03,0:20:02.36,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Mist?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.95,0:20:05.07,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Ou-Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.45,0:20:06.95,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,What's wrong, Kei-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.95,0:20:07.78,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,My teeth...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.08,0:20:10.00,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Kamogawa-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.00,0:20:15.83,Spica - Italic,,0,0,90,,My head feels so heavy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.67,0:20:20.42,Spica - Italic,,0,0,90,,My arms and legs are going numb...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.42,0:20:23.72,Spica - Italic,,0,0,90,,My vision too... What is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.64,0:20:27.05,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,What in the world is going on!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.89,0:20:33.60,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I feel sick... This is not normal at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.19,0:20:35.40,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Something must have happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.48,0:20:38.86,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,This is an emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.86,0:20:40.40,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,We have to push it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.40,0:20:41.74,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.74,0:20:43.40,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,This is a test, I'm telling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.41,0:20:44.53,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,It'll calm down in a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.53,0:20:47.03,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,What basis do you have for saying that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.03,0:20:49.03,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,We're not gonna die.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.04,0:20:50.91,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Of course we won't!\NI won't put up with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.04,0:20:56.29,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,So that's what it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.64,0:21:10.10,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,What was that just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.10,0:21:13.81,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,It made your teeth hurt and made you feel sick...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.81,0:21:17.06,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,And all of our carefully lined up dominoes... gone in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.48,0:21:21.57,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,They probably did a sudden decompression of the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.57,0:21:24.40,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Sudden decompression? An accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.40,0:21:26.15,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,This is another part of the test.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.15,0:21:27.82,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,A test? This!?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.24,0:21:34.04,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,The number of collisions between spaceships and debris has been increasing each year.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.04,0:21:37.96,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,So it's not unthinkable for there to be a major accident sometime in the future anymore.
Comment: 0,0:21:38.34,0:21:44.13,Spica - Notes,,0,0,90,,Debris: The remains of anything broken down or destroyed
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.34,0:21:39.58,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Debris?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.58,0:21:44.13,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Space garbage, like abandoned satellites and parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.13,0:21:46.72,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I-I know that much at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.35,0:21:53.85,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,If you can't keep yourself together,\Neven under those circumstances...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.85,0:21:55.81,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,...you have no business going into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.06,0:21:59.69,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,But no matter how you look at it, that's going a little too far!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.32,0:22:01.32,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Asumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.73,0:22:05.15,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Oh man, why are you shaking like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.57,0:22:07.51,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,What's wrong, Asumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.51,0:22:09.78,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Asumi! Come on, Asumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.78,0:22:11.95,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,Hey, come on...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.87,0:22:14.16,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Asumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.25,0:22:19.92,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Mo... ther...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.84,0:22:23.30,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Asumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.30,0:22:26.09,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Everyone... died...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.39,0:22:29.72,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.51,0:22:31.72,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.26,0:22:33.68,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.73,0:22:36.68,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.77,0:22:40.69,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,A memory of a day long, long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.03,0:22:50.11,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,That was...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.45,0:22:52.91,Spica - Offscreen,,0,0,90,,The Lion...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.01,0:24:36.47,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.47,0:24:40.27,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,I don't know what my late mother's face looked like.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.27,0:24:43.39,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,In art class, we ended up having to draw our family's faces...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.40,0:24:46.27,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,...and so I began to draw my mother's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.27,0:24:52.40,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,After all, I met my mother in a strange\Nworld where only dead people can go!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.20,0:24:57.37,Spica - Main,,0,0,90,,Next time on Twin Spica: My Mother's Face.